==Finnish==
===Noun===

helvetti

# ''(biblical)'' hell
# ''(expletive)'' hell, fuck, shit, devil.

Sometimes replaced by ''[[hitto]]''.

===Etymology===

''Helvetti'' is derived from Swedish ''helvete''. That sounds much like "hell knows" but doesn't necessarily mean it. In the Norse mythology, half of the heroes who succumbed in combat, went to ''Valhalla'' or ''Valhølle'', which sounds much like "hall of the chosen". 

